==English==
===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''[in]fu(n)do''  ''fu(n)dere''  ''fusi''  ''fusum'': to pour.

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-uːz|-uːz]]

===Transitive Verb===
'''infuse''' ''infusing''
# To cause to become an [[element]] of something, to [[insert]] or [[fill]]
# To [[steep]] in a liquid, so as to [[extract]] the soluable [[constituent]]s (usually [[medicinal]] or [[herbal]]).
# to [[instill]] as a quality.
#*Johnathan Swift 1667 - 1745: "Why should he desire to have qualities '''infused''' into his son,which he himself never posessed?" 
===Intransitive Verb===
# To undergo [[infusion]]
# To [[tincture]]
# to [[saturate]]
#*Let it '''infuse''' for five minutes.
